  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so that's-- when you give an affidavit, when you vouch for somebody, that was the thing that for five years you could not, you know, be supported by anyone, by the governmental authorities or so.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that was why.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They thought--they were not that anxious to employ my father, but in 1937 there were not many jobs, especially not for lawyers, and he was-- because he didn't practice law anymore here.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That was very hard on him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was very hard.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But he-- he got a job as a bookkeeper or something at Angelica.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I worked, initially, at the Shriners Hospital for Crippled-- it was called for Crippled Children at that time-- as an attendant, 12 hours night, and 12 hours day until I got a scholarship to Washington University, a full scholarship, to go to the School of Occupational Therapy, which I did.",
      "word_count": 51
    }
  ],
